"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418262","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-15","<p /> <p>No decision has been taken to close Bury Magistrates’ Court and County Court.</p><p>We will consider all identified impacts and costs once the consultation closes and all responses have been fully analysed.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418262/answer",,,,,"9878","2015-09-15T12:14:46.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418262/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418262/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-10","Magistrates' Courts: Bury","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if his Department has carried out an assessment of the effect of the closure of Bury Magistrates' Court on the (a) cost and (b) duration of journeys between local police stations and the next nearest magistrates' courts.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418263","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-15","<p>No decision has been taken to close Bury Magistrates’ Court and County Court.</p><p>We will consider all identified impacts and costs once the consultation closes and all responses have been fully analysed.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418263/answer",,,,,"9877","2015-09-15T12:14:46.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418263/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418263/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-10","Magistrates' Courts: Bury","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if his Department has carried out an assessment of the effect of the proposed closure of Bury Magistrates' Court on the (a) cost and (b) duration of journeys to the next nearest magistrates' courts for witnesses and victims of crime.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418264","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-15","<p /> <p>We are assessing the possible impacts across the criminal justice system of an increase in magistrates’ custodial sentencing powers as part of our wider court reform programme.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418264/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T12:53:11.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418264/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418264/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-10","Magistrates' Courts: Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment his Department has made of the potential increase in the use of magistrates' courts consequent upon the sentencing powers of magistrates being increased from six months to 12 months for a single offence; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418265","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-17","<p>The UK has committed a total of £600 million to the New Alliance over 3 years. This investment is split between commitments to food security, agriculture and nutrition programmes in six partner countries (Ethiopia, Tanzania, Mozambique, Ghana, Malawi and Nigeria), accounting for £480 million, and a range of wider enabling actions including policy tools and agricultural technology.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The New Alliance for Food Security and Nutrition group publish a comprehensive report on annual basis that can be found on the New Alliance website. Furthermore, every DFID programme contributing is subject to DFID’s annual review processes that are posted on the DFID Development Tracker website (http://devtracker.dfid.gov.uk/).</p><p> </p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418265/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T15:19:46.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418265/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418265/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-10","Developing Countries: Agriculture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans she has to review the level of disclosed aid through the New Alliance for Food Security and Nutrition Group.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","9902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418266","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-09-17","<p>I refer the Rt hon. Member to the reply given to the hon. Member for Lancaster and Fleetwood, Cat Smith, on 16 June 2015, PQ UIN1580.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418266/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T15:59:33.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418266/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418266/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-09-10","Ivory: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether the Government plans to bring forward legislation to ban the sale of ivory in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","9901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418267","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-17","<p>Local planning authorities have powers to decline applications if they have previously refused permission for two or more substantially similar applications on the same site, or if a substantially similar application has been rejected by the Secretary of State on appeal or following call-in, within the past two years. These powers are set out in Sections 70A and 70B of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418267/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T12:39:48.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418267/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418267/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-10","Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether any mechanism is in place for communities to prevent previously refused planning applications being repeatedly re-submitted in a slightly different form.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","9899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418268","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-17","<p>The market value of a property can be relevant to tax liability. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) will target such cases for enquiry to ensure that tax is not understated. HMRC works with expert valuers in the Valuation Office Agency where valuation is disputed.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In most cases, undervaluation of a property will be a mistake by the taxpayer or, in some cases, evasion. HMRC already has the powers needed to tackle such misdeclarations. At the July Budget, this Government announced additional investment in HMRC to tackle non-compliance.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418268/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T15:20:34.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418268/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418268/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-10","Property: Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make an assessment of the prevalence of undervaluing properties for sale; and what steps he is taking to tackle tax avoidance arising from practice.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","9900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418269","Department of Health","false","2015-09-17","<p>The Department does not make support available to men experiencing family isolation. Local commissioners are responsible for ensuring that health services match the needs of the population. However, in 2012 the Department announced that local authorities would now be expected to identify areas where older people suffer most acutely from loneliness to allow them to tackle the growing problem of social isolation and its harmful effects.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Research clearly shows that loneliness can affect health, increasing the risk of heart disease, putting people at greater risk of blood clots and dementia, and making them more likely to exercise less and drink more. Socially isolated and lonely adults are also more likely to undergo early admission into residential or nursing care. The new measure of social isolation, launched as part of the updated Adult Social Care Outcomes Framework for 2013/14, is part of a package of plans to addressing the challenges of caring for an ageing population.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government knows that there are links between mental ill health and social factors like isolation and family breakdown. <em>Preventing suicide in England: A cross-government outcomes strategy to save lives</em>, published in 2012, identified a number of high risk groups who are priorities for prevention young and middle-aged men. The Strategy recognises that factors associated with suicide in men include family and relationship problems including marital breakup and social isolation. Those who work with men in different settings, especially primary care, need to be particularly alert to the signs of suicidal behaviour.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418269/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T16:07:28.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418269/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418269/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-09-10","Mental Health Services: Males","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether his Department makes support available to men experiencing family isolation.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","9903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418270","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","true","2015-09-18","<p>All countries of the UK contributed to the funding of the 2012 Olympic and Paralympic Games. The initial £410m National Lottery contribution, outlined in the Games bid, was supplemented with a further £675m borrowed as part of the increased Olympic budget. The total transfer from the National Lottery Distribution Fund was £1,085m.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>An estimated £114m (taken from across both the £410m and £675m amounts) was the share given by Lottery programmes in Scotland. This includes amounts transferred from distributors operating wholly in Scotland, and notional amounts allocated to Scotland by UK-wide distributors.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418270/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T11:38:25.813Z","2015-09-21T11:01:12.073Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418270/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418270/answer","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418270/answer/previousversion/22213","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-09-10","National Lottery: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the sum of money received was from the National Lottery Good Causes programme in Scotland for use in funding the 2012 London Olympics.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","9904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418271","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-09-18","<p>There is a robust commitment in place to pay back £675m to the National Lottery Distribution Fund (NLDF). This funding was borrowed from the Fund in addition to the original contribution of £410m.</p><p> </p><p>It is expected that the NLDF will start to receive funds from the early 2020s through land development and sales in the Olympic Park. Scottish good causes will benefit from their portion of this reimbursed funding.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418271/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T11:42:56.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418271/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418271/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-09-10","National Lottery: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to reimburse the National Lottery Good Causes programme in Scotland for the sum of money used from that programme for use in funding the 2012 London Olympics.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","9905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418272","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-09-18","<p>Repayment of the additional £675m borrowed from the National Lottery Distribution Fund (NLDF) will start from the early 2020s.</p><p> </p><p>In addition to this repayment, £69m was transferred to the NLDF from The Olympic Lottery Distribution Fund (OLDF) when it closed in January 2015, representing a share of the income from the sale of the Olympic Village. This adds to the £79 million (from savings in the Olympic Programme) which was transferred from the OLDF to the NLDF in July 2014. The OLDF funds are allocated in the usual proportions, as set out in legislation.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418272/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T11:45:33.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418272/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418272/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-09-10","National Lottery: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what is the sum of money that has so far been reimbursed to the National Lottery Good Causes programme in Scotland for money used from that programme for funding the 2012 London Olympics.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","9906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418273","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-09-18","<p>Lottery funding shares are set out in legislation. Currently health, education, environment and charitable causes are apportioned 40%, Sport 20%, Arts 20% and Heritage 20% across the UK. Creative Scotland received 1.78% and sportscotland received 1.62% of overall lottery funding in 2014/15. In addition, Scottish good causes receive funding from the four UK-wide distributors: British Film Institute, UK Sport, Heritage Lottery Fund and Big Lottery Fund.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418273/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T11:49:58.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418273/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418273/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-09-10","National Lottery: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of the monies from National Lottery ticket sales goes to the National Lottery Good Causes programme in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","9907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418274","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-15","<p /> <p>There are no plans to treat existing ESA claimants as new applicants when they are reassessed for employment and support allowance following the enactment of the Welfare Reform and Work Bill.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418274/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T13:01:15.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418274/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418274/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-10","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether, on the enactment and coming into force of the Welfare Reform and Work Bill, the Government plans for people with an existing condition who are reassessed for the employment and support allowance work-related activity group to be classified as new applicants.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","9873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418275","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-15","<p /> <p>The Centre for Health and Disability Assessments (CHDA), a MAXIMUS UK subsidiary, currently employs 28 mental health function champions. A telephone service is provided by these mental health function champions due to the large number, and varying size of Assessments Centres across England, Scotland and Wales. These staff provide the service across all parts of the United Kingdom.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418275/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T13:02:37.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418275/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418275/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-10","Work Capability Assessment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many mental health champions are employed by Maximus in (a) Scotland and (b) the UK as part of the employment and support allowance work capability assessment process.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","9874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418276","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-15","<p /> <p>There are no formal performance measures around the role of the mental health champion.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418276/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T10:55:43.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418276/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418276/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-10","Work Capability Assessment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what evaluation he has made of the effectiveness of the role played by mental health champions in the work capability assessment process.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","9875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418277","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-15","<p /> <p>The holding of specific mental health qualifications is not a DWP requirement for healthcare professionals conducting assessments. The information requested is therefore not readily available. However, the comprehensive training provided to all healthcare professionals includes the functional effects of a wide range of mental health conditions.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418277/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T10:53:31.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418277/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418277/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-10","Work Capability Assessment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many assessors employed by Maximus under their contract to conduct work capability assessments in (a) Scotland and (b) the UK have a mental health qualification.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","9876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418278","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-15","<p /> <p>Work on reviewing how assessments can be better geared towards helping to get people prepared for and into work, if and when they are ready for that, has already begun following the Secretary of State’s speech on 24 August.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418278/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T10:57:42.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418278/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418278/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-10","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he plans to commence the review of the work capability assessment process.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","9916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418279","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-15","<p>HM Revenue and Customs publishes a monthly summary of tax and National Insurance Contributions receipts. The most recent summary was published on 21<sup>st</sup> August 2015. This is available online at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/hmrc-tax-and-nics-receipts-for-the-uk" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/hmrc-tax-and-nics-receipts-for-the-uk</a> and includes monthly Inheritance Tax receipts up to and including July 2015.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418279/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T15:57:52.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418279/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418279/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-10","Inheritance Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much inheritance tax was collected in each of the last twelve months for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418280","Home Office","false","2015-09-16","<p>I refer the hon Member to the answer I gave on 10 September 2015, to the hon Member for Newport West, Paul Flynn.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418280/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T17:00:21.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418280/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418280/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-10","Terrorism: Arrests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have been arrested on charges related to terrorist plots and intelligence gathered which led to the military action on Reyaad Khan.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","9955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418281","Cabinet Office","false","2015-09-15","<p>Any such support has been provided through Government lawyers.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418281/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T16:22:34.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418281/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418281/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-09-10","Iraq Committee of Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much the Government has spent on legal advice for recipients of Salmon Letters in the Iraq Inquiry.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","9949"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418282","Attorney General","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Serious Fraud Office (SFO) announced in August 2012 that the Director had opened a criminal investigation into allegations concerning GPT and aspects of the conduct of their business in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.</p><p> </p><p>I can confirm that the SFO has executed a search warrant and a number of arrests have been made in relation to this matter.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418282/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T14:16:24.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418282/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418282/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-09-10","GPT Special Project Management","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what progress has been made on the Serious Fraud Office's investigation into allegations of bribery in the GPT Special Project Management programme; and when he expects the investigation to conclude.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","9930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418283","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Government’s long-term economic plan seeks to rebalance growth across the UK, and build a Northern Powerhouse. Investing in digital and innovation, science, technology, transport, culture and tourism, alongside devolving power gives the North a powerful new voice, investment and decision-making powers.</p><p> </p><p>Better, faster fixed and mobile broadband drives economic growth, innovation and excellence, enhances national competitiveness, and underpins the government’s long-term economic plan.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has committed over £131 million to provide superfast broadband for nearly 1 million premises in the North of England broadband project areas.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is supporting Tech North, which will help develop and champion the digital economy. This month Tech North launched Northern Stars to showcase and support digital start-ups. The Department of Culture Media and Sport is providing £2 million per year funding for Tech North. Capital spending is also planned on tech business incubators in Manchester, Leeds and Sheffield.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is supporting new opportunities that digital technologies are unlocking, such as the sharing economy. There will be pilots in Leeds and Manchester to trial local sharing initiatives, for example in transport, public space, and health and social care.</p><p> </p><p>Companies in the North have also benefited from the availability of connection vouchers of up to £3,000 to upgrade their broadband connectivity.</p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418283/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T16:06:20.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418283/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418283/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-09-10","Digital Technology: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he plans to take to encourage the growth of the digital economy as part of the Northern Powerhouse initiative.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","9853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418284","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-17","<p>The North West fund has invested the following:<br><br>a) 3 small and medium enterprises in Pendle constituency have recieved £1.26 million investment to date.<br><br>b) 43 small and medium enterprises in Lancashire have received £20.06 million investment to date.<br><br>c) 386 small and medium enterprises in the North West have recieved £124.34 million investment to date.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418284/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T12:41:58.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418284/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418284/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-10","Small Businesses: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what information his Department holds on how many small and medium enterprises in (a) Pendle constituency, (b) Lancashire and (c) the North West have received funding from the North West Fund.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","9854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418285","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-17","<p>The North West Fund has wound down the level of marketing and promotion of the Fund due to the limited amount of funding remaining for the rest of the North West (excluding Merseyside) under the current European Regional Development Fund 2007-13 programme.<br><br>DCLG are currently working with the North West Local Enterprise Partnerships to agree the establishment of a new fund providing access to finance for small and medium enterprises under the 2014-20 programme. Once established the new North West fund will be promoted to small and medium enterprises and closely aligned with the local growth hubs providing business support.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418285/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T15:48:32.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418285/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418285/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-10","Small Businesses: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he plans to take to (a) raise awareness of and (b) encourage  small and medium enterprises in the North West to access funding from the North West Fund.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","9855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418287","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-09-15","<p>My rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change met the Chinese Special Representative on Climate Change Xie Zhenhua at the Major Economies Forum in Luxembourg in July and when she visited Beijing at the end of July. They agreed on the importance of getting an effective climate change agreement at the UNFCCC Conference of the Parties in December in Paris and agreed to work together for an ambitious outcome.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>During her recent trip, the Secretary of State also met with Minister Bekri who leads China’s National Energy Administration and a number of other Chinese stakeholders from business and government where we discussed low carbon cooperation. The Secretary of State hopes to meet with Minister Bekri again shortly for further discussions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418287/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T17:06:00.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418287/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418287/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-09-10","Environment Protection: China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what recent discussions she has had with her Chinese counterpart on areas of cooperation on green growth.","false","Biography information for Craig Williams","Cardiff North","Craig Williams","9838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418288","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-15","Our Embassy in Kabul regularly meets Hazara representatives to discuss minority issues and Hazaran representation in the National Unity Government, including 2nd Vice President Danish in September; Chief Executive Officer (CEO) Abdullah’s adviser, Dr Habibi Sorabi, in June; and 2nd Deputy to the CEO Abdullah, Mohammed Mohaqeq, in March, where concerns regarding the kidnaps of Hazaras were raised. We raised our concerns regarding minority rights with the Government of Afghanistan during Afghanistan’s Universal Periodic Review at the UN Human Rights Council in 2014.","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418288/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T14:28:04.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418288/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418288/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-10","Afghanistan: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his Afghan counterpart on the treatment of the Hazara people in that country.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","9842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418289","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-18","<p>The military action in Raqqa on 21 August 2015 was in response to armed attacks being planned and directed against the UK and was the only feasible way of disrupting them.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418289/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T13:23:13.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418289/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418289/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-10","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what criteria he uses to determine the viability of strikes against terrorist targets in states against whom the UK is not at war; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","9888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418290","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-17","<p>The UK's Reaper Remotely Piloted Air Systems operate under the same Rules of Engagement (ROE) as manned aircraft. UK ROE comply with UK and International Law.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418290/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T15:07:26.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418290/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418290/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-10","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what rules of engagement his Department has developed for strikes using unmanned aerial vehicle systems against terrorist targets in states against which the UK is not at war other than Syria; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","9887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418291","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-18","<p>Matthew Rycroft, the UK’s Permanent Representative to the UN wrote to the President of the Security Council on 7 September. This was circulated to UNSC members and published as a document of the Security Council with reference S/2015/688. As is normal in these circumstances, there will be no response.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418291/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T09:50:27.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418291/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418291/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-10","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will publish the UN's response to the letter from the UK Permanent Representative to the UN sent on 7 September on recent action taken in Syria.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","9944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418292","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>Her Majesty's Government has two policies under which locally employed civilians may be relocated to the UK.</p><p>Our Ex-Gratia redundancy scheme offers relocation to the UK to some 500 current and former local staff made redundant as a result of the drawdown of forces announced on 19 December 2012.</p><p>Our Intimidation Policy assists all current and former local staff members regardless of dates or length of employment, whose safety has been threatened because of their work with us. Staff may also be relocated either locally or to the UK, should this be required to ensure their safety in the face of employment-related intimidation. Thirty staff have been relocated locally under this policy and one person has been relocated to the UK.</p><p>These policies are kept under review to ensure their effectiveness.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418292/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T16:24:04.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418292/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418292/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-10","Afghanistan: Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his policy is on the relocation to the UK of interpreters who have worked for the British Army in Afghanistan.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","9840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418293","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>Over the last six months we relocated the following numbers of Locally Employed Staff (LES) including former interpreters and their immediate families.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Month</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>LES</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Immediate Family</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>25</p></td><td><p>42</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April</p></td><td><p>19</p></td><td><p>25</p></td><td><p>44</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>26</p></td><td><p>50</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June</p></td><td><p>39</p></td><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>48</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>33</p></td><td><p>51</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>119</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>126</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>245</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Visas have been issued for a further 32 LES and 65 family members who we expect to be relocated shortly. Visa applications for the relocation of 80 LES and 160 family members are being processed.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418293/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T15:02:52.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418293/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418293/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-10","Afghanistan: Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many interpreters who have worked for the British Army in Afghanistan have been relocated to the UK in each of the last six months.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","9841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418294","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>Ministry of Defence Lawyers will be involved in the strategic elements of the initial preparation and deployment which includes the legal basis and parameters, through to the operation itself and the post operational legal issues including any resulting litigation against the department or its personnel</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418294/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T15:04:15.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418294/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418294/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-10","Army: Legal Opinion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what legal support is provided by his Department to members of the British Army in cases related to military combat operations within the UK.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","9866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418295","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>The deployment of the British Army in combat operations in the UK is provided for under Royal Prerogative.</p><p>The legal authority to use Service personnel in operations under Military Aid to the Civil Authorities (MACA) is governed by the Civil Contingencies Act 2004 and the Emergency Powers Act 1964 (Section 2).</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418295/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T15:04:52.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418295/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418295/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-10","Army: Rules of Engagement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what statutory provisions provide for members of the British Army to conduct military combat operations in the UK.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","9867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418296","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-15","<p>My Department holds regular discussions with the Research Councils, including on cost effectiveness and their ability to compete internationally for the best researchers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As announced in Budget 2014, Research Council Institutes have been exempted from the wider public sector pay cap.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418296/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T15:57:11.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418296/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418296/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-10","Research: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether his Department has had discussions with Research Councils on the effect of pay freezes by that body on the research sector.","false","Biography information for Owen Thompson","Midlothian","Owen Thompson","9917"
