"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417886","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-23","<p>In 2010 the coalition government inherited a deficit of 10.2 per cent of gross domestic product (GDP) – the largest since the Second World War. With such a high deficit, it is inevitable that debt has continued to rise. Over the last parliament the government made substantial progress towards stabilising the public finances, halving the deficit from its post-war peak to 5 per cent of GDP in 2014-15. The Office for Budget Responsibility have forecast that debt as a percentage of GDP peaked in 2014/15, and this year will fall for the first time in 14 years as a result of the government’s actions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The table below provides Public Sector Net Debt (excluding public sector banks) and debt interest expenditure figures for each year in the period 2003/04 to 2014/15. For net debt, the figures are provided in both nominal terms and as a percentage of GDP; for debt interest, the figures are given in nominal terms and pounds sterling per capita.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td colspan="2"><p>Public Sector Net Debt<sup>1</sup></p></td><td colspan="2"><p>Debt Interest<sup>2</sup></p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p>£ billion</p></td><td><p>% of GDP</p></td><td><p>£ billion</p></td><td><p>£ per capita</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2003/04</p></td><td><p>394.2</p></td><td><p>31.8</p></td><td><p>22.0</p></td><td><p>367</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2004/05</p></td><td><p>449.2</p></td><td><p>34.4</p></td><td><p>24.6</p></td><td><p>407</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2005/06</p></td><td><p>492.0</p></td><td><p>35.5</p></td><td><p>26.3</p></td><td><p>432</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2006/07</p></td><td><p>529.3</p></td><td><p>36.2</p></td><td><p>28.6</p></td><td><p>466</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007/08</p></td><td><p>561.5</p></td><td><p>36.9</p></td><td><p>31.2</p></td><td><p>505</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008/09</p></td><td><p>727.7</p></td><td><p>49.2</p></td><td><p>31.5</p></td><td><p>506</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>959.8</p></td><td><p>62.2</p></td><td><p>31.6</p></td><td><p>503</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>1102.5</p></td><td><p>68.8</p></td><td><p>46.6</p></td><td><p>736</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>1192.0</p></td><td><p>72.3</p></td><td><p>49.7</p></td><td><p>780</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>1300.0</p></td><td><p>76.8</p></td><td><p>48.9</p></td><td><p>762</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>1403.2</p></td><td><p>79.1</p></td><td><p>48.7</p></td><td><p>753</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>1486.5</p></td><td><p>80.8</p></td><td><p>45.2</p></td><td><p>696</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="5"><p>1: Excluding public sector banks; by convention, GDP is a 12 month average centred at the financial year end. Source: ONS.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="5"><p>2: The per capita figure is calculated by dividing debt interest in £'s by the ONS estimate of the size of the UK population at the financial year end. Note that the population estimate for 2014/15 is a forecast, based on the latest ONS projections. Source: ONS.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417886/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-23T15:34:52.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417886/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417886/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-09","Public Sector Debt","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, for each year from 2003–4 to 2014–15 inclusive, (1) what was the national debt, expressed in (a) monetary terms, and (b) as a percentage of gross domestic product, and (2) what interest was paid on that debt, expressed in (a) monetary terms, and (b) in per capita terms.","false","Biography information for Lord Kinnock",,"Lord Kinnock","HL2119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417887","Home Office","false","2015-09-22","<p>The UK will continue to use the established UNHCR process for identifying and resettling refugees. We are in discussion with the UNHCR on the precise criteria for selecting cases for the expanded resettlement scheme. However, we are clear that the most vulnerable cases will be prioritised and we will only resettle those people that we and the UNHCR agree require resettlement in a country like the UK.</p>",,"Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417887/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-22T15:16:30.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417887/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417887/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-09","Syria: Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what guidance and restrictions they have given to the UNHCR about the selection of Syrian refugees for resettlement in the United Kingdom.","false","Biography information for Lord Mawhinney",,"Lord Mawhinney","HL2120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417888","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-21","<p>Relations with France on migration issues continue to be strong. At the end of July, we hosted a joint inter-ministerial conference in London to discuss how we can tackle migration pressures upstream (including from Syria) together. The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), and the Secretary of State for the Home Department, my right hon. Friend the Member for Maidenhead (Mrs May), have been in close touch with their French counterparts in recent weeks. We share a moral responsibility to help refugees and Britain is playing its part. UK ships remain in the Mediterranean and have rescued 6,700 people. The UK is contributing more than £1billion to tackle the humanitarian crisis in Syria and we will resettle 20,000 Syrian refugees over the next five years.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417888/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-21T14:47:22.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417888/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417888/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-09","Syria: Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their assessment of how diplomatic and political relations with France would be affected if they continue with their policy of admitting to the United Kingdom for resettlement only those refugees from Syria who are presently in camps near that country.","false","Biography information for Lord Mawhinney",,"Lord Mawhinney","HL2121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417889","Home Office","false","2015-09-22","<p>We intend to resettle 20,000 Syrians in need of protection during this Parliament. We will continue to work closely with the UNHCR to identify appropriate cases, prioritising the most vulnerable. As the expanded scheme is based on need and reliant on the UNHCR and other partners to make it work, it is not possible or appropriate to set any sort of annual target, but we are clear that we want to help people as quickly as possible.</p>",,"Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417889/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-22T15:39:26.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417889/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417889/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-09","Refugees: Syria","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their estimate of how many Syrian refugees will arrive in the United Kingdom for resettlement in the next 12 months.","false","Biography information for Lord Mawhinney",,"Lord Mawhinney","HL2122"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417890","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-18","<p>Welfare is a devolved matter in Northern Ireland. The Government is clear that we will not fund a more generous welfare system in Northern Ireland than elsewhere in the United Kingdom. The Northern Ireland Executive is, however, free to make more resources available for welfare from within its block grant.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417890/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T11:59:15.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417890/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417890/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-09","Social Security Benefits: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether it remains their policy that state benefits in Northern Ireland, and the qualifications to receive such benefits, should remain the same as those in England.","false","Biography information for Lord Mawhinney",,"Lord Mawhinney","HL2123"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417891","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-18","The UK regularly raises the issue of water supplies in the Occupied Palestinian Territories with the Israeli authorities. The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), and the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), did so with Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu during his visit to the UK on 10 September.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417891/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T12:09:51.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417891/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417891/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-09","West Bank: Water","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel concerning its imposition of restrictions on access to water for Palestinians in the West Bank and East Jerusalem.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2124"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417892","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-18","While the British Government has not raised this specific issue with the Israeli authorities, we do raise our concerns regarding the treatment of the Bedouin, including in the Negev. The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), and the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), raised the issue of the Bedouin with Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu during his visit to the UK on 10 September.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417892/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T12:09:44.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417892/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417892/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-09","Israel: Bedouin","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel about the family living in the Negev at Wadi Atir whose water tank was removed by Israeli soldiers during a heatwave as part of a demolition.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2125"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417893","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-18","<p>The British Government has not made and is not planning to make any representations to the Government of the United States about the number of US nationals currently living in settlements in the West Bank. However, we are in regular dialogue with the US about the harmful effects of continued Israeli settlement activity. The UK position on this is clear. Israeli settlements are illegal under international law and present an obstacle to peace which takes us further away from a two state solution.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417893/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T12:09:17.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417893/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417893/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-09","West Bank","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they are making to the government of the United States about the number of United States nationals currently living in settlements in the West Bank.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417894","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-18","<p>Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv raised the issue of the investigation with the Israeli Defence Minister on 10 September. We have called on the Israeli authorities to ensure that those responsible for this crime are brought swiftly to justice.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417894/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T12:08:30.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417894/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417894/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-09","West Bank: Crimes of Violence","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel about the progress of the investigation into the death of Ali Saeed Dawabsheh in Duma village near Nablus.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417895","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-18","The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), and the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), discussed the issue of the use of live fire by the Israel Defence Forces with Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu during his visit to the UK on 10 September. Our Ambassador in Tel Aviv also raised our concerns over the use of live fire with the Israeli Chief Military Advocate General on 27 August.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417895/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T12:02:51.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417895/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417895/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-09","Israel: Armed Forces","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they are having with the government of Israel about the review of live-fire regulations.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417896","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-18","Our Ambassador in Tel Aviv raised the issue of the Al Aqsa Mosque and Temple Mount/Haram al Sharif compound on 1 September with the Israeli Cabinet Secretary. An official from our Embassy also raised this issue with the Deputy Head of Foreign Affairs at the Israeli National Security Council on the same day. It is vital that the longstanding status quo of the Temple Mount/Haram al Sharif compound be preserved and we urge the Israeli authorities to comply with their obligations under international law as an occupying power in East Jerusalem.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417896/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T12:02:21.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417896/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417896/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-09","Israel: Religious Buildings","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what concerns they have expressed to the government of Israel about the temporal and spatial restrictions on the entry for Muslims to Al Aqsa Mosque in East Jerusalem.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2129"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417897","Department for Education","false","2015-09-18","<p>The government has no targets for opening new academies. On the basis of actual opening dates since May 2015 and anticipated opening dates of current academy proposals, between May 2015 and May 2016 approximately 650 new academies will open; this number is very likely to change as new projects arise.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417897/answer",,,,,"HL2131 ; HL2132","2015-09-18T13:20:03.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417897/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417897/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-09-09","Academies","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many new academy schools they estimate will open in the year May 2015 to May 2016.","false","Biography information for Lord Touhig",,"Lord Touhig","HL2130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417898","Department for Education","false","2015-09-18","<p>The government has no targets for opening new academies. On the basis of actual opening dates since May 2015 and anticipated opening dates of current academy proposals, between May 2015 and May 2016 approximately 650 new academies will open; this number is very likely to change as new projects arise.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417898/answer",,,,,"HL2130 ; HL2132","2015-09-18T13:20:03.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417898/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417898/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-09-09","Academies","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their target for opening new academy schools in the year May 2015 to May 2016.","false","Biography information for Lord Touhig",,"Lord Touhig","HL2131"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417899","Department for Education","false","2015-09-18","<p>The government has no targets for opening new academies. On the basis of actual opening dates since May 2015 and anticipated opening dates of current academy proposals, between May 2015 and May 2016 approximately 650 new academies will open; this number is very likely to change as new projects arise.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417899/answer",,,,,"HL2130 ; HL2131","2015-09-18T13:20:02.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417899/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417899/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-09-09","Academies","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their target for opening new academy schools in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Lord Touhig",,"Lord Touhig","HL2132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417900","Department for Education","false","2015-09-18","<p>On Monday 7 September 2015 my Rt Hon Friend the Secretary of State for Education and I attended the Academy Ambassadors ‘businesses in schools’ event, at which the Secretary of State urged business leaders to set up more academy trusts. I set up Academy Ambassadors (AA) to recruit sponsors and high-calibre business leaders to join academy trust boards as non-executive directors. This latter activity is to help multi-academy trusts grow in a sustainable way, offer specific support such as Chair of Audit or Finance, or simply serve as strong, independent board members. AA work closely with academy trusts to recruit non-executive directors and trustees with the specific skill-set the trust requires, from their local community. Its most successful approaches have been through business breakfasts, partnerships with large employers, and working with network organisations (such as Women in Banking and Finance). AA has placed over 80 business leaders onto academy trusts and has a current ‘talent pool’ of over 150 business people.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the Department for Education’s Regional Schools Commissioners undertake a wide range of activities to encourage sponsorship involving schools, businesses and other bodies, including colleges and universities, in their regions.</p><p> </p><p>The value of sponsorship is largely unquantifiable in purely monetary terms.</p><p> </p><p>Since May, no new schools have opened where the sponsor had ‘applied’ since May, however, we regularly receive applications from organisations wishing to be academy sponsors.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417900/answer",,,,,"HL2134 ; HL2135","2015-09-18T13:18:20.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417900/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417900/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-09-09","Academies","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many sponsors have applied to open new academy schools since May.","false","Biography information for Lord Touhig",,"Lord Touhig","HL2133"
