"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417902","Department for Education","false","2015-09-18","<p>On Monday 7 September 2015 my Rt Hon Friend the Secretary of State for Education and I attended the Academy Ambassadors ‘businesses in schools’ event, at which the Secretary of State urged business leaders to set up more academy trusts. I set up Academy Ambassadors (AA) to recruit sponsors and high-calibre business leaders to join academy trust boards as non-executive directors. This latter activity is to help multi-academy trusts grow in a sustainable way, offer specific support such as Chair of Audit or Finance, or simply serve as strong, independent board members. AA work closely with academy trusts to recruit non-executive directors and trustees with the specific skill-set the trust requires, from their local community. Its most successful approaches have been through business breakfasts, partnerships with large employers, and working with network organisations (such as Women in Banking and Finance). AA has placed over 80 business leaders onto academy trusts and has a current ‘talent pool’ of over 150 business people.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the Department for Education’s Regional Schools Commissioners undertake a wide range of activities to encourage sponsorship involving schools, businesses and other bodies, including colleges and universities, in their regions.</p><p> </p><p>The value of sponsorship is largely unquantifiable in purely monetary terms.</p><p> </p><p>Since May, no new schools have opened where the sponsor had ‘applied’ since May, however, we regularly receive applications from organisations wishing to be academy sponsors.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417902/answer",,,,,"HL2133 ; HL2134","2015-09-18T13:18:20.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417902/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417902/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-09-09","Academies","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their total estimated value of sponsorship for new academy schools between 7 May and 31 August.","false","Biography information for Lord Touhig",,"Lord Touhig","HL2135"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417903","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-25","<p>Trading Standards are the designated enforcers for the ticketing provisions in Chapter 5 of Part 3 of the Consumer Rights Act 2015 and cases of non-compliance should be brought to their attention. Consumers can report the matter through the Citizens Advice consumer helpline (03454 04 05 06) who will pass complaints onto Trading Standards where appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>where the issue is one of fraud or e-crime, this should be reported to Action Fraud the UK’s national fraud and internet crime reporting centre, (http://www.actionfraud.police.uk/report_fraud).</p><p>This applies to the RBS 6 Nations Series as well as other future events.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417903/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-25T12:27:24.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417903/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417903/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-09","Rugby: Tickets","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action they have taken regarding the sale of tickets for the 2016 RBS 6 Nations series that are being offered for sale before being released by the organisers on secondary-market websites that do not provide the details required under the Consumer Rights Act 2015.","false","Biography information for Lord Moynihan",,"Lord Moynihan","HL2136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417904","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-02","<p>Her Majesty's Government is satisfied that it has a clear understanding of the constraints on legislation imposed by the Consumer Rights Directive and has not to date sought discussions with the European Commission on this matter.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417904/answer",,,,,,"2015-10-02T13:16:05.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417904/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417904/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-09","Tickets: Sales","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the European Commission to ascertain whether it would be in accordance with the EU Consumer Rights Directive for both primary- and secondary-market ticket sellers to have to provide a unique reference number so that event organisers can track sales of tickets.","false","Biography information for Lord Moynihan",,"Lord Moynihan","HL2137"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417905","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-24","<p>We have no plans to change the enforcement provisions of the secondary ticketing rules in the Consumer Rights Act 2015 which only came into force on 27 May 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417905/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-24T10:00:48.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417905/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417905/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-09","Tickets: Touting","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they are considering increasing the maximum penalty that can be imposed on secondary-market operators for breaching the Consumer Rights Act 2015.","false","Biography information for Lord Moynihan",,"Lord Moynihan","HL2138"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417906","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-25","<p>The review which we will announce shortly will welcome contributions from all stakeholders in the sector.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417906/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-25T12:30:51.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417906/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417906/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-09","Tickets: Touting","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they plan to announce the chair, membership and terms of reference of the group conducting the statutory review into the secondary ticketing market; and whether they plan to include representatives from the Rugby Football Union, the Glastonbury Festival, and the security management team at The O2 on the proposed panel of experts.","false","Biography information for Lord Moynihan",,"Lord Moynihan","HL2139"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417907","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-30","<p>It is not possible to give an estimate of the total number of websites that have been shut down with the help of City of London Police. In the financial year 2014-15, 6029 websites were disrupted with the assistance of the City of London Police; and in 2013-14, 2365 websites were disrupted.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Trading Standards have lead responsibility for enforcing the online secondary ticketing provisions of the Consumer Rights Act 2015 and information on interventions in relation to websites is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417907/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-30T14:04:45.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417907/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417907/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-09","Tickets: Touting","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their latest estimate of the total number of websites that have been shut down with the help of City of London Police to date; and how many websites have agreed to remove Rugby World Cup tickets from their websites as a result of secondary-market operators being in breach of the Consumer Rights Act 2015.","false","Biography information for Lord Moynihan",,"Lord Moynihan","HL2140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417908","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-18","<p>We have no plans at present to propose to the UN Secretary-General that he commission such a study.</p><p>Resolving the ongoing Ethiopia-Eritrea border dispute requires both countries to engage in political dialogue. We believe this would be in the economic interests of both countries, and contribute to reducing instability in the Horn of Africa.</p><p>We have consistently urged both Eritrea and Ethiopia to engage bilaterally and with international partners, such as the EU and the UN, to overcome the current stalemate. The UK, along with our partners in the international community, has underlined that the decision by the Ethiopia-Eritrea Boundary Commission is final and binding. We urge both governments to respect the commitment they made in the Algiers peace agreement of December 2000.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417908/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T12:01:39.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417908/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417908/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-09","Eritrea: Ethiopia","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to propose to the UN Secretary-General that he commission a study of the effects on the economies of Eritrea and Ethiopia if the latter gave their unequivocal approval to the boundary demarcation between the two states, as determined by the Eritrea-Ethiopia Boundary Commission.","false","Biography information for Lord Avebury",,"Lord Avebury","HL2141"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417909","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-16","<p>Her Majesty’s Coastguard does not have a boat based in Belfast.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417909/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T13:29:00.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417909/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417909/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-09","Rescue Services: Belfast","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government why the coastguard boat based in Belfast was given an Irish Language name; and what steps they plan to take to ensure equality of cultures in any such namings in the future.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL2142"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417910","Leader of the House of Lords","false","2015-09-21","<p>My office makes regular contact with all Government departments that are unable to meet the 10 working day target within which to answer Questions for Written Answer. Every effort is made to address delays and to remind departments of their responsibilities to Parliament.</p><p>I have recently taken the opportunity to discuss the need for timely answers with all members of the Government front bench in this House, and written to the five departments with the greatest proportion of late responses in the 2014/15 session to make clear the House’s expectations and to stress the importance of timely responses. My office will continue to work with all departments to ensure prompt and satisfactory answers to Questions for Written Answer.</p><p>The delay in the particular case to which the noble Lord refers related to delays in gathering the required data. The question tabled by Lord Falconer of Thoroton on 21 July has now been answered.</p>",,"Baroness Stowell of Beeston","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417910/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-21T14:45:20.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417910/answer","Biography information for Baroness Stowell of Beeston","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417910/answer",,,,,"92",,"Leader of the House of Lords","2015-09-09","Ministry of Justice: Written Questions","2","House of Lords","To ask the Leader of the House what explanation she has received from the Ministry of Justice about the failure to answer Lord Falconer of Thoroton's Question for Written Answer tabled on 21 July, before Wednesday 9 September, 25 working days after an answer was due.","false","Biography information for Lord Jopling",,"Lord Jopling","HL2143"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417974","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>The misconduct process relating to Ministry of Defence Police officers based at the Atomic Weapons Establishment Burghfield has not yet been fully concluded. Once completed, a report will be prepared by the Chief Constable and submitted to the Independent Police Complaints Commission.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417974/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T15:00:06.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417974/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417974/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-09","Ministry of Defence Police: Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 27 January 2015 to the hon. Member for Moray to Question 222334, what the conclusions are of the Ministry of Defence Police Professional Standards investigation into disciplinary matters relating to police officers based at the Atomic Weapons Establishment, Burghfield; and if he will place a copy of that investigation report in the Library.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","9672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417975","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-09-15","<p>Civil nuclear safety and security are priorities for the Government. The Office for Nuclear Regulation (ONR) regulates safety and security at UK licenced nuclear sites and site licensees are required to demonstrate appropriate security plans against a range of relevant threats, which are updated on an on-going basis. The details of these threats are not released on grounds of National Security.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417975/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T16:53:25.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417975/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417975/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417975/answer/previousversion/21297","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-09-09","Nuclear Power Stations: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps her Department has taken to protect nuclear power stations from attacks carried out using unmanned drones.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","9821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417976","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-16","<p>The names, dates and locations of nuclear weapons accident response exercises that have taken place or are scheduled between 1 January 2015 and 31 December 2016 are provided below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Exercises Conducted </strong></p><p><strong>(1 Jan 2015 to present)</strong></p><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>Date</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Location</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senator Slick</p></td><td><p>March 2015</p></td><td><p>Suffolk</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Orange Eagle</p></td><td><p>June 2015</p></td><td><p>Berkshire</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Osmosis</p></td><td><p>July 2015</p></td><td><p>Suffolk</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Open Isotope</p></td><td><p>July 2015</p></td><td><p>Suffolk</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Diamond Dragon</p></td><td><p>July 2015</p></td><td><p>Suffolk</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Exercises Scheduled </strong></p><p><strong>(present to 31 Dec 2016)</strong></p><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>Date</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Location</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Astral Climb / Osmosis</p></td><td><p>November 2015</p></td><td><p>Nottinghamshire</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Orange Eagle</p></td><td><p>March 2016</p></td><td><p>Berkshire</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Osmosis</p></td><td><p>June 2016</p></td><td><p>Dumfries &amp; Galloway</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Open Isotope</p></td><td><p>June 2016</p></td><td><p>Dumfries &amp; Galloway</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Astral Climb</p></td><td><p>June 2016</p></td><td><p>Dumfries &amp; Galloway</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Astral Bend / Osmosis</p></td><td><p>September 2016</p></td><td><p>Oxfordshire</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Open Isotope</p></td><td><p>September 2016</p></td><td><p>Oxfordshire</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417976/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T14:09:32.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417976/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417976/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-09","Nuclear Weapons: Emergencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the name, date and location is of each nuclear weapons accident response exercise which (a) has taken place or is planned in 2015 and (b) is scheduled for 2016.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","9807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417977","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>We regularly review all major programmes, including those relating to the nuclear deterrent, to ensure that they continue to operate in the most efficient and effective manner possible.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417977/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T15:07:59.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417977/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417977/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-09","Ministry of Defence: Nuclear Installations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans to publish the results of his review of the defence nuclear enterprise.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","9808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417978","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-17","<p>There were no incidents of unauthorised access to nuclear weapons and material. Defence Ministers were notified of four security incidents in 2013-14 and three security incidents in 2014-15 at defence nuclear sites. The Office for Nuclear Regulation security categorisation does not apply to defence.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417978/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T15:04:52.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417978/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417978/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-09","Nuclear Installations: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many reportable nuclear security incidents at defence sites he was notified of in the financial years (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2014-15; and for each of these years, how many incidents were classified as (i) major, (ii) moderate, (iii) minor and (iv) of no significance according to the categorisation used by the Office for Nuclear Regulation.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","9806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417979","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-17","<p>There are a number of organisations within the Ministry of Defence (MOD) who have responsibility for maintaining and monitoring nuclear security at defence sites. MOD Head Office sets security policy for defence including the requirements for nuclear security. The responsibility for the delivery of nuclear security at defence nuclear sites rests with the Head of Establishment. Nuclear security assurance (monitoring) is delivered through self assurance by the defence nuclear site. Independent assurance is provided through the Principal Security Advisors to Front Line Commands and the Defence Equipment and Support organisation and through MOD Head Office.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417979/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T15:05:26.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417979/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417979/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-09","Nuclear Installations: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which offices in his Department are responsible for maintaining and monitoring nuclear security at defence sites.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","9805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417980","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>Consistent with industry best practice, Pegasus is under regular review to ensure it meets the Ministry of Defence's requirements effectively. There is no specific closing date for this activity as it will continue through the life of the project.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417980/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T15:07:07.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417980/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417980/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-09","AWE Aldermaston: Nuclear Reactors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when the Atomic Weapons Establishment review of how best to achieve the customer requirements for Project Pegasus was (a) started and (b) completed.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","9803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417981","Prime Minister","false","2015-09-16","<p>As my statement to the House on Monday 7 September made clear, at a meeting of the most senior members of the National Security Council, it was agreed that should the right opportunity arise, military action should be taken. The Attorney General attended the meeting and confirmed that there was a legal basis for action. Information about the detail of internal proceedings and discussions are not normally disclosed.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417981/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T12:12:49.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417981/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417981/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-09-09","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, pursuant to his statement of 7 September 2015, Official Report, column 26, on Syria: refugees and counter-terrorism, whether the meeting of the National Security Council to which he referred was provided with the full written advice to Government, a summary of that advice or a verbal statement by the Attorney General on the legal basis for the military action against Reyaad Khan.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","9748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417982","Home Office","false","2015-09-14","<p>As the Prime Minister said in his statement to the House (7 Sep 2015: Column 26), it would be inappropriate to comment further.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417982/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-14T15:23:29.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417982/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417982/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-09","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Prime Minister's statement of 7 September 2015, Official Report, column 26, on Syria: refugees and counter-terrorism, how many terror suspects have been (a) arrested and (b) prosecuted in the UK in association with the six attempts to attack the UK.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","9749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417983","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-16","<p>DFID has recently completed two project reviews for humanitarian work in the Central African Republic and with Central African Republic refugees. These reviews will shortly be available on our website ‘Development Tracker’.</p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417983/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T13:53:53.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417983/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417983/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-09","Central African Republic: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the timetable is for the completion of programme reviews of UK aid funding for the Central African Republic.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","9698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417984","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-16","<p>Food security for the people of Yemen is a growing concern. According to the UN, of the 12.9 million Yemenis classified as food insecure, 6 million are facing severe food shortages. In Hodeidah city alone, UNICEF has warned that 96,000 severely malnourished children are at risk of dying. The ongoing conflict has affected imports of essential fuel, food and medical supplies into Yemen. In addition, ongoing fighting is preventing the distribution of food to those who most need it.</p><p>The UK is one of the largest donors to the crisis in Yemen and has announced £55 million to help at least half a million Yemenis caught in this conflict. This is providing vital medical supplies, water, food and emergency shelter.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417984/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T14:18:53.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417984/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417984/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-09","Yemen: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment her Department has made of the likelihood and scale of food shortages in Yemen as a result of conflict in that country.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","9699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417985","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-16","<p>I refer the Right Hon. member to the answer given by my Right Hon. Friend Minister of State Tobias Ellwood on 16 September 2015 to Question 9701.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417985/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T14:18:13.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417985/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417985/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-09","Yemen: Humanitarian Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the prospects for re-establishing free and fair access for humanitarian aid to Yemen through Port Hodiedah.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","9700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417986","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-16","<p>The UK has lobbied the Saudi Arabian -led Coalition and the Yemeni Government on the importance of non-politicisation of aid, as well as the need to improve access for commercial goods and humanitarian aid, including via Hodeidah Port. The UK is supporting the UN, working with the Coalition and Yemeni Government, to make the system for verifying shipping more efficient. It is critical that Hodeidah and the other Red Sea ports be accessible for commercial and humanitarian ships. If ports do not reopen the risk of famine in Yemen will increase further. Food and medicines are needed in the north, as is fuel to transport goods, power hospitals, pump water and provide for ordinary Yemeni’s energy needs.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417986/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T11:14:52.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417986/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417986/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-09","Yemen: Humanitarian Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what action the Government is taking to secure free and fair access for humanitarian aid to Yemen via Port Hodiedah.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","9701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417987","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-17","<p>The Triennial Review of the Construction Industry Training Board (CITB), Engineering Construction Industry Training Board (ECITB) and Film Industry Training Board (FITB) took place under the Coalition Government. However it was not possible to publish the report before the May 2015 general election.</p><p> </p><p>In the Budget on 8 July 2015, the new Government announced that it will introduce a levy on large UK employers to fund post-16 apprenticeships. The Government is now consulting on how the levy should be implemented, including its interaction with the existing sector levies.</p><p> </p><p>“Given these skills funding policy changes, there have been delays in publication as we consider how the sector levies interact with the apprenticeship levy.”</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417987/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T14:29:14.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417987/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417987/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-09","Industrial Training Boards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when he plans to publish the Government response to the Industry Training Boards review, announced on 23 September 2013; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","9740"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417988","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p /> <p>No decision has been taken to close Hartlepool Magistrates’ Court and County Court.</p><p> </p><p>The consultation is open until 8 October and we will consider all identified impacts and costs once the consultation closes and all responses have been fully analysed.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417988/answer",,,,,"9760","2015-09-14T15:21:11.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417988/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417988/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-09","Magistrates' Courts: Hartlepool","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the proposed closure of Hartlepool Magistrates' Court, what estimate he has made of additional costs arising from increased expenses of (a) staff of agencies using the court system and (b) members of the public.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","9759"
