"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417459","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-18","<p>The UK has a proud record of leadership on the humanitarian response to the Syria crisis, having pledged a total of £1 billion. The UK has provided over £169 million to the UN World Food Programme (WFP) since the start of the crisis.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>WFP, like all our partners, is under intense pressure to respond to massive needs in the region and has had to make some tough choices. The UK strongly supports WFP’s efforts to target the most vulnerable in this crisis, particularly women and children. The UK is closely monitoring the situation across the region, alongside other key donors, to understand how this reduction in support will impact the lives of Syrian refugees.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK does not lobby other donors on behalf of any specific agency, but to focus their attention and their resources on supporting the overall Syria crisis response. The UK is by far the largest bilateral donor in Europe, and second only to the United States, to the Syria crisis. However the UK, the US and the European Union cannot do this alone and other donors must do more to support the needs of millions of Syrians across the region.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417459/answer",,,,,"HL2053 ; HL2054","2015-09-18T12:00:15.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417459/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417459/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-08","World Food Programme","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the UN World Food Programme's decision to reduce assistance provided to 1.6 million Syrians in refugee camps owing to budgetary constraints.","false","Biography information for Lord Boateng",,"Lord Boateng","HL2055"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417460","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-16","<p>The Road Investment Strategy sets out an intention to upgrade all remaining single carriageway sections of the A303 between the M3 and the A358 to dual carriageway standard as part of a long-term commitment to creating a new Expressway to the South West. We are starting this process with three major improvements: A303 Amesbury to Berwick Down (Stonehenge), A303 Sparkford to Illchester and the A358 Taunton (M5) to Southfields. Construction of these schemes is expected to start in the first Road Period (by 1 April 2020), depending on planning, and completion is expected by the middle of the 2020s at the latest. We would expect subsequent Road Investment Strategies to fund the remaining improvements, such as to the Illminster by-pass.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p /><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417460/answer",,,,,"HL2057","2015-09-16T13:30:11.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417460/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417460/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-08","A303","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government in which year they currently expect the dualling of the A303 around Stonehenge to be completed.","false","Biography information for Lord Cameron of Dillington",,"Lord Cameron of Dillington","HL2056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417461","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-16","<p>The Road Investment Strategy sets out an intention to upgrade all remaining single carriageway sections of the A303 between the M3 and the A358 to dual carriageway standard as part of a long-term commitment to creating a new Expressway to the South West. We are starting this process with three major improvements: A303 Amesbury to Berwick Down (Stonehenge), A303 Sparkford to Illchester and the A358 Taunton (M5) to Southfields. Construction of these schemes is expected to start in the first Road Period (by 1 April 2020), depending on planning, and completion is expected by the middle of the 2020s at the latest. We would expect subsequent Road Investment Strategies to fund the remaining improvements, such as to the Illminster by-pass.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p /><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417461/answer",,,,,"HL2056","2015-09-16T13:30:11.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417461/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417461/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-08","Roads: South West","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government in which year they currently expect the dualling of the A303 along the Ilminster by-pass and the A358 link to the M5 to be completed.","false","Biography information for Lord Cameron of Dillington",,"Lord Cameron of Dillington","HL2057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417462","Cabinet Office","false","2015-09-18","<p>We regard cyber security as one of the top risks to UK national security. The 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review therefore covers cyber security and will consider what we need to tackle the cyber threat. We cannot speculate on the outcome of the Strategic Defence and Security Review.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417462/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-18T13:16:37.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417462/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417462/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-09-08","Cybercrime","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made in the forthcoming Strategic Defence and Security Review of the threat posed by cyber security; and whether they plan to commit to new spending in this area.","false","Biography information for Lord Carlile of Berriew",,"Lord Carlile of Berriew","HL2058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417463","Cabinet Office","false","2015-09-17","<p>The UK Cyber Security Strategy, published in November 2011, sets out how the UK will support economic prosperity, protect national security and safeguard the public’s way of life by building a more trusted and resilient digital environment. The next UK Cyber Security Strategy will continue this work and will include steps to address cyber breaches and protect the UK economy from cyber attack.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417463/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T12:23:10.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417463/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417463/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-09-08","Cybercrime","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the next United Kingdom Cyber Security Strategy will outline the steps they plan to take to address cyber breaches and protect the United Kingdom economy from the threat of cyber attack.","false","Biography information for Lord Carlile of Berriew",,"Lord Carlile of Berriew","HL2059"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417464","Cabinet Office","false","2015-09-17","<p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review will look comprehensively at cyber security. We cannot speculate on the outcome of the Strategic Defence and Security Review.</p><p>The Government is already focusing its efforts on building partnerships with industry, academia and international partners. The benefits of stable and secure cyberspace show the need for shared responsibility in improving the UK’s cyber security.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417464/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-17T12:23:36.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417464/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417464/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-09-08","Cybercrime","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether, under the process of conducting the forthcoming Strategic Defence and Security Review, they considered creating a new stand-alone government office for National Cyber Security, the purpose of which would be to manage the cyber security programme and continue to develop the public sector–private sector partnership.","false","Biography information for Lord Carlile of Berriew",,"Lord Carlile of Berriew","HL2060"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417465","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-25","<p>There are currently no initiatives encouraging research into this area. The Medical Research Council (MRC) is one of the main agencies through which the Government supports medical and clinical research. It is an independent research funding body which receives its grant-in-aid from the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In keeping with the Haldane principle, decisions on specific research priorities and funding are taken by the Research Councils based on advice from the research community through peer review The MRC welcomes high quality applications for support into any aspect of human health and these are judged in open competition with other demands on funding. Awards are made according to their scientific quality and importance to human health.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417465/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-25T12:30:32.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417465/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417465/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-08","Neurofibromatosis: Research","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to ensure that medical researchers are encouraged to work in the field of neurofibromatosis type 1.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL2061"
