"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417538","Cabinet Office","false","2015-09-15","<p>Officials regularly meet with a range of external organisations to discuss the Government's objectives in Europe.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417538/answer",,,,,"9488","2015-09-15T16:20:22.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417538/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417538/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-09-08","Cabinet Office: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which external organisations officials in (a) his Department and (b) Number 10 Downing Street have met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many meetings such officials have had with each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9489"
