"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417540","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-14","<p>The government is currently considering the report produced by the Airports Commission before making any decisions on airport capacity. If a final decision has any implications for public spending, those will be worked through in the normal way at the appropriate time.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417540/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-14T14:53:03.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417540/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417540/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","London Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether public expenditure on infrastructure and access associated with a proposed new runway in South East England would be subject to the Barnett Formula.","false","Biography information for Roger Mullin","Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath","Roger Mullin","9356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417541","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-16","<p>The number of notices or demands for payment for amounts less than £1 could only be provided at a disproportionate cost. HM Revenue and Customs does not automatically collect the data on how many notices or demands for payments are issued for amounts less than £1.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417541/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T10:31:47.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417541/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417541/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Tax Collection","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many notices or demands for payment were posted to companies and individuals by HM Revenue and Customs for amounts less than £1 in each financial year since 2012-13.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bridgen","North West Leicestershire","Andrew Bridgen","9352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417542","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-11","<p>Where applicable, the UK’s Conflict, Stability and Security Fund (CSSF) spending will be counted towards the government’s commitment to spend 0.7% of GNI on Overseas Development Assistance (ODA) or 2% of GDP on Defence spending. This is completed in accordance with NATO and Organisation for Economic Co-operation &amp; Development guidelines. Some CSSF spending may count to both the ODA and Defence spending commitments, where it is consistent with the classification guidelines.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417542/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-11T11:42:58.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417542/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417542/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Conflict, Stability and Security Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, under what circumstances spending from the UK Conflict, Stability and Security Fund will be counted towards the Government targets of spending (a) 0.7 per cent of gross national income (GNI) on overseas development assistance, (b) 2 per cent of GNI on defence and (c) towards both of these targets.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","9455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417543","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-11","<p>The age 75 is a feature of the existing pensions tax system. It is the age at which individuals stop receiving tax relief on pension contributions and by which most people will have brought their pension into payment.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417543/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-11T10:43:22.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417543/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417543/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Pensions: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, by what process his Department set the age limit for passing on a pension tax free.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","9402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417544","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-14","<p>Whether the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) made an estimate of the potential liability of any banks is a matter for the FCA. However, it is reasonable to assume that for any conduct issue that arises, the FCA would seek to understand the potential financial impact.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Several meetings took place between Treasury Ministers and the FCA in January 2012 (then the Financial Services Authority), although I understand that FCA’s interest rate hedging products redress scheme was not on the agenda for any of these meetings.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417544/answer",,,,,"9411","2015-09-14T15:20:39.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417544/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417544/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Interest Rate Swap Transactions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether Ministers in his Department met representatives of the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) to discuss the FCA interest rate hedging products redress scheme in January 2013.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","9410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417545","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-14","<p>Whether the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) made an estimate of the potential liability of any banks is a matter for the FCA. However, it is reasonable to assume that for any conduct issue that arises, the FCA would seek to understand the potential financial impact.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Several meetings took place between Treasury Ministers and the FCA in January 2012 (then the Financial Services Authority), although I understand that FCA’s interest rate hedging products redress scheme was not on the agenda for any of these meetings.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417545/answer",,,,,"9410","2015-09-14T15:20:39.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417545/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417545/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Interest Rate Swap Transactions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the Financial Conduct Authority made an estimate of the potential liability of (a) Lloyds and (b) RBS under the interest rate hedging products redress scheme during the development of that scheme.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","9411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417546","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-16","<p>This Government is committed to working to eliminate child poverty and improving life chances for children.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government has carefully considered the impact of the tax and benefit reforms introduced in the Summer Budget. The intended impact of these reforms is to incentivise work, ensure work always pays, and then allow people to keep more of what they earn.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417546/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T16:32:59.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417546/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417546/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the effect on (a) relative and (b) absolute child poverty of the four year freeze announced in the Summer Budget 2015 on the uprating of (i) tax credits and (ii) child benefit.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","9470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417547","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-16","<p>The requested information is not available.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417547/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T16:42:17.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417547/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417547/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Pensions: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect on the average overall value of the pensions of people in Scotland over the course of their retirement of changes to (a) drawdown products and (b) switching retirement income products introduced in April 2015.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","9473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417548","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-16","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. The Chancellor of the Exchequer regularly meets with a range of external organisations to discuss the Government's objectives in Europe. Details of Ministerial meetings with external organisations are published quarterly.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417548/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T10:23:45.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417548/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417548/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Treasury: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which external organisations he has met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many times he has met each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417549","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-16","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Departments are appropriately resourced to support the Government’s priorities in Europe.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417549/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T10:28:49.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417549/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417549/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Treasury: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many officials in his Department are engaged in research into the effects of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417550","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-16","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Officials regularly meet with a range of external organisations to discuss the Government's objectives in Europe.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417550/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T10:24:52.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417550/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417550/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Treasury: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which external organisations officials in his Department have met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many meetings such officials have had with each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417551","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-11","<p>Social investment is the provision of finance to generate social and financial returns.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417551/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-11T11:40:54.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417551/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417551/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Social Enterprises: Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what definition of social investment is used by his Department.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","9608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417552","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-11","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials have regular meetings with departments in which a wide range of issues are discussed as part of the process of policy development. However we do not disclose details of confidential discussions between Ministers or advice received from civil servants.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417552/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-11T11:44:47.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417552/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417552/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent discussions he has had with his Cabinet colleagues on the use of technology in (a) making savings to the public purse and (b) improving public services.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","9611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417553","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-16","<p>This Government is committed to working to eliminate child poverty and improving life chances for children.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government has carefully considered the impact of the tax and benefit reforms introduced in the Summer Budget. The intended impact of these reforms is to incentivise work, ensure work always pays, and then allow people to keep more of what they earn.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417553/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T10:33:47.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417553/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417553/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the effect on (a) relative and (b) absolute child poverty of (i) the two child limit for the child element of Tax Credit; and (ii) the removal of the family element of Child Tax Credit announced in the July Budget.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","9627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417554","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-16","<p>At Summer Budget the government reiterated the need to continue to take tough decisions on public sector pay, in order to improve the public finances while protecting the quality of public services and jobs.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Therefore the government announced that it will fund public sector workforces for an average pay award of 1% for 4 years from 2016-17 onwards. This will save approximately £5 billion by 2019-20.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417554/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T10:22:36.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417554/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417554/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Public Sector: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department has made of the savings that will accrue to the public purse from capping public sector pay increases at 1 per cent in each of (a) 2016-17, (b) 2017-18, (c) 2018-19, (d) 2019-20 and (e) 2020-21.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","9624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417555","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-11","<p>Distributional analysis of the impact of government policy across the household income distribution has been published at every fiscal event since the June Budget 2010.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The analysis published alongside the Summer Budget shows that the proportion of public spending received by households in each income quintile remains similar between 2010-11 and 2017-18, indicating that reductions in public spending since the start of the last Parliament have not altered its overall distribution.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417555/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-11T10:44:53.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417555/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417555/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Budgets","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make it his policy to publish an analysis of the distributional impact of changes alongside each Budget Statement in this Parliament.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","9644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417556","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-16","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) does not produce forecasts for future VAT payable on the Severn Bridge Tolls. Even if HMRC was to do so, the information would be based upon previous VAT receipts and so the statutory duty of taxpayer confidentiality would prevent it from being disclosed.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417556/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T14:45:45.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417556/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417556/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Severn River Crossing: Tolls","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much his Department expects to be raised in VAT on Severn Bridge tolls in (a) 2015, (b) 2016, (c) 2017 and (d) 2018.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","9658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417557","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-14","<p>The relevant information from the last two Joint Exchequer Committees, as agreed by the UK and Scottish Governments, has been published online, and can be found in the following locations on gov.uk:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>7<sup>th</sup> July: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/joint-exchequer-committee-communique-7-july-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/joint-exchequer-committee-communique-7-july-2015</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>4<sup>th</sup> September: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/joint-exchequer-committee-4-september-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/joint-exchequer-committee-4-september-2015</a></p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417557/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-14T15:30:13.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417557/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417557/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Joint Exchequer Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he plans to publish the minutes and papers from the last two meetings of the Joint Exchequer Committee; and if he will place those documents in the Library.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","9662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417558","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Treasury considered OBR’s forecasts of inflation and public sector workforce size before announcing the policy of a one per cent cap on public sector pay increases in the Summer Budget 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The latest OBR forecasts are published alongside the Summer Budget 2015, and are available here: <a href="http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/economic-fiscal-outlook-july-2015/" target="_blank">http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/economic-fiscal-outlook-july-2015/</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417558/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-14T15:09:24.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417558/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417558/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Public Sector: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assumptions his Department made about the likely percentage growth of public sector pay in (a) 2016-17, (b) 2017-18, (c) 2018-19, (d) 2019-20 and (e) 2020-21 before announcing the policy of a one per cent cap on public sector pay increases in the Summer Budget 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","9659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417559","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-16","<p>The information requested can be found in table 2.1 of the Summer Budget and is available here:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443232/50325_Summer_Budget_15_Web_Accessible.pdf</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417559/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-16T14:46:52.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417559/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417559/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-08","Inheritance Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department has made of the effect on revenue accruing to the Exchequer of restricting the additional nil-rate inheritance band (a) to residences only, (b) to direct descendants only and (c) by tapered withdrawal between £2,000,000 and £2,350,000.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","9660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417560","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-15","<p>The current estimate of the Department for Transport is that the level of the outstanding debt following the end of the Severn River Crossings concession will be £88 million. This money is due to be repaid to the consolidated fund.</p><p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p><strong></strong></p><p> </p><p><strong></strong></p><p /><p><strong></strong></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417560/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T14:16:51.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417560/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417560/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-08","Severn River Crossing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the amount of debt that will remain outstanding after the current concession for operating the Severn Bridge expires; and between which bodies that debt will be distributed.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","9661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417561","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Officials regularly meet with a range of organisations to discuss the Government's objectives in Europe.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417561/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T11:44:46.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417561/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417561/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Department for Communities and Local Government: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, which external organisations officials in his Department have met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many meetings such officials have had with each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417562","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-15","<p>Provisions we are seeking in the Cities and Local Government Devolution Bill, if enacted, will allow a local authority to propose a reduction in the number of councillors as part of a devolution deal.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417562/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T16:09:49.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417562/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417562/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Councillors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to reduce the number of local government elected representatives.","false","Biography information for Stephen McPartland","Stevenage","Stephen McPartland","9471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417563","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Departments are appropriately resourced to support the Government’s priorities in Europe.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417563/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T11:41:32.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417563/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417563/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Department for Communities and Local Government: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many officials in his Department are engaged in research into the effects of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417564","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Departments are appropriately resourced to support the Government's priorities in Europe.<br><br>The Secretary of State regularly meets with a range of external organisations to discuss the Government's objectives in Europe. Details of Ministerial meetings with external organisations are published quarterly.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417564/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T11:44:13.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417564/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417564/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Department for Communities and Local Government: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, which external organisations he has met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many times he has met each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9532"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417565","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-11","<p>My rt. hon. Friends, the Home Secretary and the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government are leading a Joint Committee to put in place the necessary arrangements to expand the existing Syrian Vulnerable Persons Relocation Scheme to resettle up to 20,000 Syrians in need of protection during this Parliament.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Secretary will provide an update to the House next week.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417565/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-11T12:53:50.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417565/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417565/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Housing: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make it his policy that local authorities each house 10 refugee families; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","9493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417566","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-11","<p>The Care and Support Specialised Housing Fund will provide up to £315 million over 5 years for specialised housing for older and disabled people. Phase 1 of the fund will deliver over 4,000 new affordable homes and the bids for phase 2 are currently being assessed.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417566/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-11T12:52:45.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417566/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417566/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Housing: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to increase the number of accessible homes for people with (a) muscular dystrophy, (b) neuromuscular conditions and (c) other progressive conditions.","false","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","9457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417567","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-11","<p>The Government has invested just over £1 billion in the Disabled Facilities Grant since 2010. When the cost of the adaptation exceeds the maximum limit, local authorities have the discretion to provide additional funding. The future funding of the Grant is a matter for the Spending Review.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417567/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-11T12:52:11.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417567/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417567/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Disabled Facilities Grants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to ensure that the statutory maximum grant available for a Disabled Facilities Grant increases in line with inflation.","false","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","9458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417568","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-15","<p>Information on social housing lettings is collected in the Department through the COntinuous REcording of Social lettings (CORE). From April 2013 to March 2014, there were 8,597 social housing lettings made to people under 18 years old, 9% (738) of which lived with a child in the same household. Of these, 14 tenants were under 16 and 21% (3) of them had a child in the same household.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417568/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T11:40:51.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417568/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417568/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Social Rented Housing: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many people (a) under 18 and (b) under 16 years of age have been allocated social housing since 2013; and what proportion of such people had children of their own.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417569","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-11","<p>Our £500 million investment in local authority and voluntary sector homelessness services has contributed to local authorities preventing 935,800 households from becoming homeless since 2010. Together with other Departments, we are considering the overall level of funding for local government through the Spending Review.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417569/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-11T12:51:21.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417569/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417569/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Homelessness Prevention Grant; and what his future plans are for this policy.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","9390"
