"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417572","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. The Secretary of State regularly meets with a range of external organisations to discuss the Government's objectives in Europe. Details of Ministerial meetings with external organisations are published quarterly.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417572/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-14T14:21:45.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417572/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417572/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-09-08","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, which external organisations he has met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many times he has met each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9533"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417573","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Departments are appropriately resourced to support the Government’s priorities in Europe.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417573/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-14T14:19:01.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417573/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417573/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-09-08","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many officials in his Department are engaged in research into the effects of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417574","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-09-15","<p>I am committed to ensuring that the benefits of sport can be realised by all communities across the country. Whilst there have been no meetings specifically on this issue recently, I am always open to discussions with colleagues around the country and Sport England has a specific remit to work at all levels, for example funding the County Sports Partnerships which work directly with local councils.</p><p> </p><p>We are currently consulting on our new sport strategy and will of course be taking devolved and regional issues into consideration as part of this. Earlier this year the Department for Culture, Media and Sport ministers signed the UK up to take part in the first ever European Week of Sport - the European Commission’s new initiative to promote sport and exercise in local communities across Europe, working with Sport England, Sport Wales, Sport Scotland and Sport Northern Ireland.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417574/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-15T08:48:34.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417574/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417574/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-09-08","Exercise and Sports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions Ministers in his Department have had with regional and devolved administrations on promoting sport and exercise in local communities.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","9479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417575","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Officials regularly meet with a range of external organisations to discuss the Government's objectives in Europe.</p><blockquote><p> </p></blockquote>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417575/answer",,,,,,"2015-09-14T14:20:21.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417575/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417575/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-09-08","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, which external organisations officials in his Department have met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many meetings such officials have had with each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417576","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-16","<p /> <p>According to TV Licensing's data, in 2014 232,290 women and 114,347 men were interviewed under caution by TV Licensing officers in the course of investigating TV licence offences.</p><p> </p><p>The number of people prosecuted for licence fee evasion in 2014 is published here: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/428943/cjs-outcomes-by-offence-data-tool.xls" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/428943/cjs-outcomes-by-offence-data-tool.xls</a> From “offence” drop down list select 191A Television licence evasion. From “sex” drop down list select the male or female.</p><p> </p><p>In 2014 11 men and 28 women were committed to prison for non-payment of a fine where the registered fine was for non-payment of the TV Licence. The average time spent in prison was 18 days for men and 20 days for women.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417576/answer",,,,,"9632","2015-09-16T10:42:03.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417576/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417576/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Television: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many (a) women and (b) men were found to be using a television without a licence by inspectors in the most recent year for which information is available; and what proportion of (i) women and (ii) men were subsequently prosecuted for a television licence offence.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9560"
